description._content: Catalog #: 09_01643 Title: First Lieutenant Harry Haw Special Collection Photo Long Beach California Additional Information: The 514th Observation Squadron at Long Beach Summer Camp, 1937. Left to right. Front row: Lt. John J. Mulvey, Lt. C.A. Biram, Lt. Harry Haw, Capt. Cedric B. Davis, Lt. Wm A. Speer, Lt. Warren D. Brockman and Capt. James A. Moore. Back row: Lt. Joseph S. Wakefield,m capt. Frank H. Page, Capt. Lester J. King, Lt. Clinton B. Gaty, Lt. Douglas J. Kelly, Lt. W. L. Van Dusen and Lt. Charlie A. Longaker. Not in picture: Capt. Walter W. Grosa, capt. W.W. Mounts and Lt. Lyal C. Woods, Harry Haw served in the U.S. Army in the 514th Observation Squadron. He entered the U.S. Army in 1917 and became a First Lieutenant in 1930. He became a civilian Transport Pilot by 1930 and had logged 789 flying hours by 1934. he later became Principal of the Alice Birney school.
